headline: Did Mixed Q4 Results and Higher 2026 Guidance Just Shift TKO Group Holdings' (TKO) Investment Narrative?
summary: In February 2026, TKO Group Holdings reported fourth-quarter 2025 sales of US$1,038.1 million with a small net loss, full-year 2025 sales of US$4.74 billion with improved net income of US$195.4 million, and issued 2026 revenue guidance targeting US$5.68 billion to US$5.78 billion. The combination of a loss-making quarter, much stronger full-year profitability and higher revenue targets for 2026 gives investors a more complex picture of how TKO is balancing growth, costs and earnings quality...
